begin_memory_text: At the beginning of the conversation we talked about where we were from and we chatted about that for a little bit
middle_memory_text: We talked about politics and the pandemic and how it has become too politicized.
end_memory_text: We talked about how fun it was to talk to someone new during this time and to share those thoughts and emotions.
rest_of_day_open: This is Monday and the start of the week, so basically anything can happen. The plan right now is to go out on Friday and look for a cat to adopt, but something could pop up during the week that could derail that plan. Overall I see the week going fairly well.
critical_positive: I think what worked well the most was that there were no technical difficulties during the conversation. We could hear and see each other clearly throughout. Also, it was very helpful to be paried with someone that had good energy and was genuinely interested in the conversation. That helped a ton.
critical_negative: I think the thing that didn't work well in the conversation was that you felt a little pressured to keep the conversation going throughout. You don't want there to be any "dead air" between the two of you and with the clock running in the background you feel a slight sense of performance.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we lived, he lived in Jersey, which made me bring up Tv shows with people from Jersey and that he was a teacher, and how the pandemic has affected his job.
middle_memory_text: We talked about politics and different views and issues we have going on right now in America and views on voting.
end_memory_text: We talked about social media and how it affects people-especially young people- today. And what social media we use and don't use and why.
rest_of_day_open: Hopefully, it will go well. I don't foresee any major lows or by major highs. Just hoping to get through another week with my family and myself safe and healthy. We are doing schooling from home for the kids and I am currently working from home so I see us spending a good ninety percent of our time at home this week, due to the pandemic and also, the weather.
critical_positive: I think that we had similar work backgrounds gave us an ice breaker to figure out what else we could talk about. I am a pretty open person and like to have discussions with people about many different topics of interest and my partner seemed like he was as well.
critical_negative: There were a few times where I felt unsure of what to talk about next. With the pandemic and elections going on I find myself slightly worried about saying something that could come off wrong or make someone upset. But my partner was very nice and did not make me feel uncomfortable.
